            <title><![CDATA[A CSS Logo Hatches!]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[
          <img style="display: none" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dnpmdb8r8/image/upload/argyleink/css-logos.png" alt="The 3 CSS logo variants next to each other, primary, light and dark." height="1399" width="3715" />
        <p>With <a href="https://github.com/CSS-Next/css-next/issues/105#issuecomment-2471590502"><strong>400</strong> votes</a>, <code>rebeccapurple</code> is the community chosen logo color for CSS! This puts a bow on the concept we&#39;ve been working on with the community 💜</p>
<style>article > p > img {
  border-radius: 0;
}</style>

<p><img 
            loading="lazy" 
            src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dnpmdb8r8/image/upload/f_auto,c_limit,q_auto,w_auto/w_600/argyleink/csslogo.png" 
            alt="" 
            title="Title " 
            decoding="async"
            width="300" 
            height="300"
          /></p>

        <h2>
          New repo
          <a name="new-repo" href="#new-repo">#</a>
        </h2>
       <p>Checkout the <a href="https://github.com/CSS-Next/logo.css">shiny new repo</a> that will hold the logo, alt formats, and eventually <a href="https://github.com/CSS-Next/logo.css/issues/11">variants for CSS4, CSS5, and beyond</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/CSS-Next/logo.css">github.com/CSS-Next/logo.css</a></p>

        <h2>
          Big thanks
          <a name="big-thanks" href="#big-thanks">#</a>
        </h2>
